HEADWORD: Shortage
<hw>Short"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Amount or extent of
deficiency, as determined by some requirement or standard; <as>as, a
<ex>shortage</ex> in money accounts</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Short-breathed</ent>⟦br⟧
